snippet.textDisplay: Sean, I would like to return your thank you, because I may only be 16 but time and time again as I joined your streams I have felt guilty for not doing my part and donating. You are such a genuine person and you have brought many together. You have a way with words and a personality that keeps people excited. In this day and age with so many bad people out there you are one of the few genuine people. You have brought so many people together and gave so many people something to connect over (hi Distry) and impacted so many lives, honestly, there's not many out there who are like you. You are a kind hearted and smart man and so many people look up to you and trust you, and with that trust you are given, you return it. You have saved so many lives and helped so many people, you have a whole community who is willing to blindly follow you and yet you do not mislead any of us. So many people out there would take advantage of something like this, but you do not, and I think that I speak for many when I say that we thank you for that. We thank you for being a kind hearted and trustworthy person, an influence and example for people to follow, without you so many people would not be here today and so many more would be in a bad place. This world is a better place because of those who you have inspired. Because of your example, humanity is better than it would be if you weren't here. My comment may be overlooked or get lost with the thousands of other comments, but if by some chance you do read this, I would just like to thank you for saving mine, and so many others, lives, and making living just a bit more tolerable for those in a bad place. From the bottom of my heart, I thank you Sean, for being here when we needed you the most. Sincerely, that one fan you have never met but who has been here for three years watching as your community continues to grow ever stronger.
